                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.3335/18</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-11T20:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If this invitation will be accepted by the United States Government the Minister
                    Foreign Affairs will send me a written invitation in the following words: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Confirming our conversation of yesterday and informed of the arrival of
                            the squadron of the United States in the River Plata, I take pleasure in
                            making known to your excellency that the Argentine Government will have
                            the greatest pleasure in receiving its visit and that of the officers
                            and sailors of that friendly nation.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
